# ===========================================================================
# Custom Ollama Modelfile — ReactiveAgents runtime model
# Base: gemma4:e2b-it-qat (Google Gemma 4 edge E2B, int4 QAT -> GGUF Q4_0)
# Tuned on the RTX 4050 Laptop GPU (6 GB) per s8/a2 measurements.
# Build:  ollama create gemma4-e2b-agent -f Modelfile.gemma4-e2b-agent
# ===========================================================================
FROM gemma4:e2b-it-qat

# --- Context window --------------------------------------------------------
# 32768 (s5/d22, gate-approved). This model uses sliding-window attention
# (only 3 of 35 layers keep a global KV cache), so context is CHEAP on VRAM:
# 8192->32768 adds only ~+24 MiB KV; even 131072 fits ~1.56 GiB with ~4.1 GiB
# free (no Shared-GPU spill, no OOM). The driver of the choice is window
# OVERFLOW, not VRAM: a realistic ~18.4k-token deep-research synthesize prompt
# overflows 8192/16384 (prompt truncated -> thinking block EMPTY -> thin/empty
# report, the s5 root cause of o4); 32768 fits the full prompt WITH room for
# CoT + substantive output. CAVEAT (s8 scope): at 32768, num_predict=4096
# becomes the OUTPUT limiter (thinking+content fill 4096) for long reports.
PARAMETER num_ctx 32768

# --- Deterministic structured output --------------------------------------
# temperature 0 measured 8/8 valid JSON AND 8/8 valid plan-DAG on the real
# planner prompt (think disabled). top_p/top_k kept at gemma's sane bounds.
PARAMETER temperature 0
PARAMETER top_p 0.95
PARAMETER top_k 64
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.0

# --- Output budget ---------------------------------------------------------
# With THINKING DISABLED (the runtime passes the API field think=false on
# structured calls) the planner JSON is ~376 eval tokens; 1024 is a safe
# content ceiling. NOTE: if a call ENABLES thinking (think=true) for richer
# plans, it must raise the per-request num_predict to ~4096 to fit the
# chain-of-thought trace before the JSON content — otherwise the CoT runs past
# the cap and the content comes back EMPTY (the s8/a2 root-cause).
PARAMETER num_predict 1024

# --- System prompt ---------------------------------------------------------
# Neutral fallback only. The ReactiveAgents runtime sends its OWN system
# message per task (planner factory description / composed spec rulesets),
# which Ollama uses in preference to this default — so this is just a sane
# baseline for a bare /api/generate call and does NOT fight the agent.
SYSTEM """You are the local reasoning model for the ReactiveAgents app. Be precise and follow the caller's output-format instructions exactly."""

# --- Runtime knobs that are NOT Modelfile params (set by server/transport) --
# * think=false  -> request field on /api/chat (disables CoT for structured
#                   output; the decisive agentic-fitness lever). Not bakeable.
# * keep_alive   -> request field or OLLAMA_KEEP_ALIVE env; use "30m" or -1 to
#                   keep the model warm (cold load ~8-10 s -> warm TTFT ~0.38 s).
# * Server env (set on `ollama serve`): OLLAMA_FLASH_ATTENTION=1,
#   OLLAMA_NUM_PARALLEL=1, OLLAMA_MAX_LOADED_MODELS=1. Leave KV cache at the
#   default f16 (q8_0/q4_0 gave NO VRAM benefit on this SWA model and cost ~5%
#   tok/s).
